post_text:
The Families First Coronavirus Response Act allows states to issue Food Assistance benefits to households with children in grades PK-12 who temporarily lost access to free or reduced-price school meals due to pandemic-related school closures. Any child who was enrolled this past school year AND received free or reduced-price school meals as of March 16 is eligible. The amount provided is $307.80 per eligible child.

Visit the Iowa Department of Education's website for more information. https://www.educateiowa.gov/article/2020/07/07/dhs-announces-pandemic-food-assistance-distribution-plan?utm_source=July+9%2C+2020&utm_campaign=SUMMER+%40+DMPS+Update&utm_medium=email

post_text: The meals program was approved and begins tomorrow Friday, March 20. A breakfast and lunch will be available daily. Lunch for the day and breakfast for the next day will be distributed at the same time. Pick ups will be at 5 locations - at the school buildings in Manly and Nora Springs and the following locations: In Hanlontown (City Park), Plymouth (by post office) and Rock Falls (Mail Boxes by Park). Pick up time is from 11:00 am to noon Monday through Friday. If you have not filled out the survey to sign up for lunches, you will need to do that to receive the lunches. The head cooks check this daily. Thank you. https://forms.gle/vmdKY1WH4uBtKZoG7

post_text:
What an unbelievable showing we had at the District Track meet on Friday night! Central Springs will be participating in a total of 19 events between the boys and girls. 29 of our student athletes will be representing Central Springs in Des Moines on Thursday, Friday & Saturday! We have had inquiries about a pep bus traveling to Des Moines to cheer on the Panthers. We will have a sign up starting today in the high school office and if we have enough 9-12th grade students signed up to ride on Thursday and/or Friday (at least 25 each day) a pep bus will provide transportation to the state track meet. There will be no cost for the bus but each student is responsible for their own cost of admission, food, etc.

Please sign up in the high school( for 9th-12th grade students) office as soon as possible if you would like to ride the pep bus on Thursday, May 16th and/or Friday, May 17th.

post_text: Recently, Central Springs was awarded $25,000 through the America‚Äôs Farmers Grow Rural Education grant. We were able to purchase a Lincoln Electric virtual welder for use in Mr. Dobel‚Äôs industrial technology classroom. This Friday night, October 12th, from 5 - 7 PM we are hosting an open house and invite anyone from our communities to stop in and check out this new technology. Please use the school door on the southeast corner of the building to enter the shop. Between the 1st and 2nd quarter of the football game we will be recognized by Bayer Agriscience for our winning grant. If you are a farmer who nominated Central Springs for this grant, we would love to see you at the game to be recognized as well, and we want to especially thank you for nominating us! Without your support, this opportunity for our students would not be possible.

We were able to purchase a Lincoln Electric virtual welder for use in Mr. Dobel‚Äôs industrial technology classroom. This Friday night, October 12th, from 5 - 7 PM we are hosting an open house and invite anyone from our communities to stop in and check out this new technology. Please use the school door on the southeast corner of the building to enter the shop. Between the 1st and 2nd quarter of the football game we will be recognized by Bayer Agriscience for our winning grant. If you are a farmer who nominated Central Springs for this grant, we would love to see you at the game to be recognized as well, and we want to especially thank you for nominating us! Without your support, this opportunity for our students would not be possible.
